DECISION: A single run is 20 minutes, structured in three acts. Act One (0–5 min) is a Prep Period — mission locations are hidden, the player builds their loadout through milestone-based power selections, and movement is open but carries risk: stumbling into a mission location before the prep period ends makes that mission live immediately. Act Two (5–15 min) is the Open Window — all three mission locations reveal simultaneously on the map, and the player has full agency to attempt a mission immediately or continue developing their loadout. Act Three (15–20 min) is Forced Commitment — the game forces a mission choice at the 15-minute mark, and the player executes with whatever they have built. Mission locations are randomized each run; no mission type has a fixed geographic location. Locations are visible once revealed and can be stumbled upon before reveal during the prep period.

DATE: May 3, 2026

WHY: 20 minutes is substantial enough to feel meaningful and short enough to sustain a one-more-run impulse. The three-act structure gives every run dramatic shape — preparation, decision, commitment. The forced choice at 15 minutes ensures build decisions carry weight by creating a moment of reckoning with whatever the player has accumulated. Randomized mission locations support narrative variety and prevent the world from feeling scripted or repetitive.

